        <descriptionSet>
            <description>This folio depicts the universe as a Ptolemaic system informed by the medieval church. The Earth forms the center (with an inverted landscape), followed by spheres of water, air and fire, the 7 known planets, the firmament and its crystal ceiling and the prime moving force.  The ethereal world follows in a crescent containing God and the celestial beings. The geocentric view of the universe would be supplanted by Nicolas Copernicus, who proved the sun was the center of the universe in 1530.</description>
